BREAKING: The scene at the Rayburn Building is pure rebellion. Protesters are swarming in during live hearings on Medicaid cuts.

Security’s losing control. Because when the government wages war on the poor, the poor fight back.

The Rayburn Building is on fire with protest.

People are swarming the halls during live hearings on Medicaid cuts.

Security can’t contain it — because when the government wages war on the poor, the poor fight back.

This isn’t chaos. This is a reckoning.

(1/)

This isn’t just about Medicaid.

It’s about decades of policies that punish the struggling while the rich get tax breaks and subsidies.

And now, people are saying enough.

This is what resistance looks like in real time.

(2/)

That’s why I wrote F*ck Around & Find Out: The 50-State Civic Uprising Manual

Because protests like this don’t happen in a vacuum — they happen because people are organizing, strategizing, and refusing to stay silent

This book shows you exactly how to take that energy and build lasting power

(3/)

In this book, you’ll learn:
-How to mobilize in your state when policies threaten your community
-How to organize actions like these — with impact
-How to turn a protest into a movement
We’re not waiting for permission anymore.

We’re building power on our own terms.

(4/)

If you’re watching this and asking, “What can I do?”

This book is your blueprint.
F*ck Around & Find Out isn’t just about outrage — it’s about equipping you to act.

Grab your copy now and join the movement:
🔗 https://stan.store/gxldsociety/p/fck-around--find-out

(5/)

Ever been part of a protest that felt like a turning point?

Drop your story — and let’s talk about what comes next.

record.text: Incredible. The Trump administration calculated "tariff rates" by taking the US trade deficit with the respective country and dividing it by the country's exports to the US. And then the tariff rate of the US is often just set by cutting that made-up "tariff rate" in half.

Furthermore, the Trump admin only used the trade deficit in goods. And if the US balance of trade with a country is roughly even (or trade deficit to imports is less than 10%), the tariff rate is listed as 10%.

posts.content: Incredible. The Trump administration calculated "tariff rates" by taking the US trade deficit with the respective country and dividing it by the country's exports to the US. And then the tariff rate of the US is often just set by cutting that made-up "tariff rate" in half.
